{"type":"message","id":"4048d25c","parentId":"707ab2c9","timestamp":"2026-05-12T11:26:03.123Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The output file is garbled due to the big5/cp950 encoding issue. Let me check if the knowledge base was generated properly and also test if ray-v3 works with actual prompts.\n\nLet me try a direct test with curl through the Python subprocess to test the ray-v3 model properly. Also let me check if the model is actually responding or just returning empty.\n\nActually, I notice the API test returned empty response (`Response: ` with nothing after it). This means qwen3.5:4b (and ray-v3) might be generating thinking but then returning empty text. Let me investigate.\n\nActually wait - looking at the API response, when I used `stream: False`, it returned empty. But when I used streaming mode, the process showed the thinking content but the actual response was empty. \n\n\nLet me try a simpler approach to get the model to respond. I think the issue might be that qwen3.5:4b in thinking mode produces a very long internal chain before the actual output, and the output might be getting cut off or misinterpreted. Let me try a different approach to verify the model is working correctly.\n\nLooking at the timing, 16.5 seconds for an empty response is typical for qwen3.5:4b when it's doing its thinking process. The real problem is that the thinking block dominates the output, so the actual response appears empty. I need to either disable thinking or drastically increase the timeout.\n\nLet me check if there's an environment variable or setting to turn off thinking, or I could try a more focused prompt without the system context to see if that helps.\n","thinkingSignature":"c8df5ca4f256ccaa4fcca2d3c186eb4f68fdd9f9a853b4222fdcc0dd8cde36dc"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_bfenww09ciyd_1","name":"write","arguments":{"content":"import urllib.request, json, time\n\n# Test qwen3.5:4b directly first\nmodels_to_test = [\n    (\"qwen3.5:4b\", \"你是什麼？回答3個字。\"),\n]\n\nfor model, prompt in models_to_test:\n    print(f\"\\n=== Testing {model} ===\")\n    data = {\n        \"model\": model,\n        \"prompt\": prompt,\n        \"stream\": False,\n        \"options\": {\n            \"temperature\": 0.3,\n            \"num_predict\": 30,\n            \"num_ctx\": 512\n        }\n    }\n\n    body = json.dumps(data).encode(\"utf-8\")\n    req = urllib.request.Request(\n        \"http://localhost:11434/api/generate\",\n        data=body,\n        headers={\"Content-Type\": \"application/json\"}\n    )\n\n    start = time.time()\n    try:\n        with urllib.request.urlopen(req, timeout=60) as resp:\n            raw = resp.read().decode(\"utf-8\")\n            result = json.loads(raw)\n            response = result.get(\"response\", \"EMPTY\")\n            print(f\"Response: '{response}'\")\n            print(f\"Thinking done: {result.get('done', False)}\")\n            print(f\"Load duration: {result.get('load_duration', 0)/1000000000:.1f}s\")\n            print(f\"Total duration: {result.get('total_duration', 0)/1000000000:.1f}s\")\n    except Exception as e:\n        print(f\"Error: {e}\")\n    print(f\"Wall time: {time.time()-start:.1f}s\")","path":"C:\\Users\\USER\\.openclaw\\agents\\ray\\test_all_models.py"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":4619,"output":717,"cacheRead":74688,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":80024,"cost":{"input":0.0013857,"output":0.0008604,"cacheRead":0.00448128,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.00672738}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778585141798,"responseId":"065241366bbc1383edce94676bc85618"}}
