{"type":"message","id":"70dd1e4f","parentId":"c81b6fcf","timestamp":"2026-05-12T11:33:35.582Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_6yegkgxikdsc_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"=== response ===\r\n\r\n=== thinking (last 300 chars) ===\r\n  *   Tone: Professional, knowledgeable, helpful, but honest about limitations.\r\n    *   Language: Traditional Chinese.\r\n\r\n3.  **Address the Core Question (\"Today's Market\"):**\r\n    *   I cannot provide real-time stock prices or market trends because my knowledge cutoff is static and I don't have a live\r\n=== done === True\r\n=== eval_count === 200"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":7184,"aggregated":"=== response ===\r\n\r\n=== thinking (last 300 chars) ===\r\n  *   Tone: Professional, knowledgeable, helpful, but honest about limitations.\r\n    *   Language: Traditional Chinese.\r\n\r\n3.  **Address the Core Question (\"Today's Market\"):**\r\n    *   I cannot provide real-time stock prices or market trends because my knowledge cutoff is static and I don't have a live\r\n=== done === True\r\n=== eval_count === 200","cwd":"C:\\Users\\USER\\.openclaw\\agents\\ray"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1778585615582}}
{"type":"message","id":"d0e3b1d4","parentId":"70dd1e4f","timestamp":"2026-05-12T11:33:55.993Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The model is generating text - but the response is empty (the actual text generation was truncated to 200 tokens by num_predict). The thinking process is there, but the actual response text is empty. And the model says \"I cannot provide real-time stock prices\" which is a disclaimer, not a useful answer.\n\nThis means the model IS working, but:\n1. The thinking takes up most/all of the 200 token limit\n2. The actual response gets cut off or is empty\n\nWith num_predict=200, we got eval_count=200 tokens, but the response field is empty. This is very strange - it means the model is generating tokens but they all go into \"thinking\" and not into \"response\".\n \nAh, I see - it's qwen3.5's dual-output structure where the thinking process lives in a separate field while the actual response goes into its own field. So the response is genuinely empty even though the thinking consumed all 200 tokens, which suggests the model spent the entire token budget on the thinking process before it could generate the actual answer.\n\nI should bump num_predict up to 500 to give the model enough room to complete both the thinking and the response, or disable thinking entirely if I just want the raw output.\n","thinkingSignature":"773edaf9d4eff020d487e587d4444088adf32a0202e837dbc3f725809f6ef699"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n\n**qwen3.5:4b 有在運作**，但有個設計特點：\n\n```\nresponse: \"\"（實際回答）\nthinking: \"Thinking Process...\"（思考過程）\ndone: True\neval_count: 200（用了 200 tokens，但全部消耗在思考上）\n```\n\n模型把幾乎所有 token budget 都花在思考過程，真正的回答被截掉了。\n\n---\n\n**解決方案：增加 num_predict，讓回答有空間輸出。**\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_oe7yb94iagev_1","name":"write","arguments":{"content":"import urllib.request, json, sys\n\nurl = \"http://localhost:11434/api/generate\"\npayload = {\n    \"model\": \"qwen3.5:4b\",\n    \"prompt\": \"你是Ray，美股Agent。用繁體中文一句話回答：今天美股可以用幾成倉位？\",\n    \"stream\": False,\n    \"options\": {\n        \"num_ctx\": 512,\n        \"num_predict\": 600,  # 給夠空間讓它輸出回答\n        \"temperature\": 0.3\n    }\n}\n\nbody = json.dumps(payload).encode(\"utf-8\")\nreq = urllib.request.Request(url, data=body, headers={\"Content-Type\": \"application/json\"})\n\nsys.stdout.reconfigure(encoding=\"utf-8\", errors=\"replace\")\ntry:\n    with urllib.request.urlopen(req, timeout=60) as resp:\n        raw = resp.read().decode(\"utf-8\")\n        for line in raw.strip().split(\"\\n\"):\n            try:\n                obj = json.loads(line)\n                response = obj.get(\"response\", \"\")\n                thinking = obj.get(\"thinking\", \"\")\n                print(\"=== 實際回答 ===\")\n                print(response if response else \"(空)\")\n                print(\"=== 思考長度 ===\", len(thinking), \"字元\")\n                print(\"=== eval_count ===\", obj.get(\"eval_count\", 0))\n                print(\"=== total_time ===\", round(obj.get(\"total_duration\", 0)/1e9, 1), \"秒\")\n            except:\n                pass\nexcept Exception as e:\n    print(f\"ERROR: {e}\")","path":"C:\\Users\\USER\\.openclaw\\agents\\ray\\test_q35.py"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":218,"output":730,"cacheRead":86208,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":87156,"cost":{"input":0.00006539999999999999,"output":0.0008759999999999999,"cacheRead":0.005172479999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0061138799999999995}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778585615584,"responseId":"06524312f32337a4fa7f9a6624de4e3b"}}
