{"type":"message","id":"b4201139","parentId":"76e6a135","timestamp":"2026-05-12T11:37:42.984Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is saying to wait longer for qwen3.5:4b to finish thinking. The issue I've been seeing is that the thinking part takes a very long time (30-60 seconds), and then the actual response seems to be empty. But maybe the model is outputting thinking tokens in the `response` field instead of the `thinking` field, and the actual answer gets cut off.\n\nLet me write a script that waits up to 120 seconds and captures the full output. Let me also try with a much longer `num_predict` to ensure the answer can come through.\n\nLet me also look at what the `done_reason` says - it said \"length\" when eval_count hit the max. So the model is hitting the token limit before it can output the answer after thinking.\n \nI think I found it - the model generates a long internal thinking process first, then tries to output the actual response, but it's hitting the token limit before completing both. Even with num_predict=2000, the thinking part alone consumes most of those tokens, so the actual response gets truncated.\n\nLet me try a different approach: I'll prefill the assistant's response to skip the thinking phase entirely, or use a system prompt to disable it. If I set thinking=false, the model might bypass the thinking tokens and just output the answer directly.\n\nThe problem is thinking isn't a supported parameter in Ollama, so that won't work. I need to find another way to structure the prompt so the model doesn't feel the need to do extensive reasoning before answering. Maybe I should try much lower temperature or change how I'm framing the question to guide the model toward direct response without the thinking overhead.\n\nActually, looking at my test output more carefully, when num_predict=10 and done_reason is \"length\", it's hitting the token limit but still not outputting anything in the response field—just the thinking field with partial content. The model might be putting its entire output into the thinking field, which suggests it's generating but not actually producing a response that gets captured.\n\nI should try increasing num_predict significantly to give the model enough room to complete both its thinking and response. And I should test whether qwen3.5:4b-mini works at all, or just go back to the models I know are functional like qwen2.5:7b or ray-v1.\n","thinkingSignature":"a3c21554eca587449c6de45b39572a9c00199b7a23c6e0e40f9d731edda10518"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n好，來個長超時完整測試：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_nlgw7bvc6xtz_1","name":"write","arguments":{"content":"import urllib.request, json, sys\nsys.stdout.reconfigure(encoding=\"utf-8\", errors=\"replace\")\n\nurl = \"http://localhost:11434/api/generate\"\npayload = {\n    \"model\": \"qwen3.5:4b-mini\",\n    \"prompt\": \"你是Ray。用繁體中文回答：今天美股可以用幾成倉位？一句話。\",\n    \"stream\": False,\n    \"options\": {\n        \"num_ctx\": 512,\n        \"num_predict\": 3000,\n        \"temperature\": 0.3,\n        \"min_p\": 0.05\n    }\n}\n\nbody = json.dumps(payload).encode(\"utf-8\")\nreq = urllib.request.Request(url, data=body, headers={\"Content-Type\": \"application/json\"})\n\nprint(\"=== qwen3.5:4b-mini 完整測試 (90s timeout) ===\")\ntry:\n    with urllib.request.urlopen(req, timeout=90) as resp:\n        raw = resp.read().decode(\"utf-8\")\n        obj = json.loads(raw)\n        response = obj.get(\"response\", \"\")\n        thinking = obj.get(\"thinking\", \"\")\n        print(f\"response: '{response}'\")\n        print(f\"response len: {len(response)}\")\n        print(f\"thinking len: {len(thinking)}\")\n        print(f\"eval_count: {obj.get('eval_count',0)}\")\n        print(f\"total_time: {round(obj.get('total_duration',0)/1e9,1)}s\")\n        print(f\"done: {obj.get('done',False)}\")\n        print(f\"done_reason: {obj.get('done_reason','')}\")\n        if thinking:\n            print(f\"\\nthinking tail (最後500字):\\n{thinking[-500:]}\")\nexcept Exception as e:\n    print(f\"ERROR: {e}\")","path":"C:\\Users\\USER\\.openclaw\\agents\\ray\\test_mini_full.py"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":1191,"output":925,"cacheRead":88512,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":90628,"cost":{"input":0.00035729999999999996,"output":0.0011099999999999999,"cacheRead":0.00531072,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.006778019999999999}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778585834761,"responseId":"065243ed4579fd5adcab66d61ad563fb"}}
